<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06033c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06033c">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06033c"> 33(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> opposing brands</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;Sir Samuel Ferguson&rsquo; <br>LAMENT FOR THOMAS DAVIS. <br> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> <br>But my trust is strong in God, Who made us brothers, <br>That He will not suffer their right hands, <br>Which thou hast joined in holier rites than wedlock, <br>To draw <mark>opposing brands</mark>: <br>Oh, many a tuneful tongue that thou mad&apos;st vocal <br>Would lie cold and silent then; <br>And songless long once more, should often-widowed Erin <br>Mourn the loss of her brave young men! <small> Alfred Perceval Graves, <a name="ILMS2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ILMS2"><cite title="source">Irish Literary and Musical Studies</cite></a>, (1913) 43</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
